;; Create IID_IDVDRenderer->AddYourRenderer mappings using this template
;;
;; If you want to select between multiple registered renderers, call
;; IDVDNavigationManager::UseRenderer(name) in your application before SetVolume().
;; If you don't call UseRenderer(), the first registry entry will be used by default.
;;
;; To register a renderer,
;;
;; 1. Create a new entry with the renderer name as the last subkey, like this:
;;       [HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\CLSID\<CLSID_Metadrvr>\<IID_IDVDRenderer>\<AddYourRendererName>]
;;
;; 2. Add a value named "Renderer" to the subkey.  The data for this value
;;    is the CLSID of the new renderer.
;;
;; 3. Optionally add a value named "BitstreamType" to the subkey. The data for this
;;    value is the bitstream type to be used in IBitstreamProcessor::SetBitstreamType()
;;    during renderer initialization. The default is 0.
;;
;; Example:
;; [HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\CLSID\{99C99C72-43E8-11d4-84C8-00C04F68EB0F}\{99C99C73-43E8-11d4-84C8-00C04F68EB0F}\MyCoolRenderer]
;; "Renderer"="{99C99C71-43E8-11d4-84C8-00C04F68EB0F}"
;; "BitstreamType"=dword:0


; @CESYSGEN ENDIF

; @CESYSGEN IF DIRECTX_MODULES_TVSHELL
; @CESYSGEN ENDIF

